Reasoning: The workbook has one sheet with columns: A=Month Available, B=Year Available, C-N=monthly values, O=Increase Based on Availability containing a formula that pulls the value for the month in column A from the same row. The user wants the formula to also consider the year: for any row where Year Available is 2022, the formula should always return the January value (the value in column C) regardless of the month in column A. For other years (e.g., 2023), the original behavior (lookup by month) should remain. Therefore we need to replace the existing formula in column O for all data rows with a new formula that checks the year and, if 2022, uses the January column, otherwise uses the month lookup. The new formula is:

    =IF($B2=2022, INDEX($C2:$N2, MATCH("Jan", $C$1:$N$1, 0)), INDEX($C2:$N2, MATCH($A2, $C$1:$N$1, 0)))

We will write this formula into every cell in column O (column 15) from row 2 to the last row. After updating, we will save the workbook to the output directory, recalculate formulas, and verify a few cells to ensure they contain the new formula.

The steps are:
1. Load the workbook.
2. Determine the max row.
3. Loop through rows 2..max_row and set ws.cell(row, 15).value to the new formula string (with the row number inserted appropriately).
4. Save to /sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet/1_39515_init.xlsx.
5. Call recalculate() on the saved file.
6. Reload the file data_only=True and print the first few column O values to confirm the formula was written.

We will now execute this plan.
Code:
```repl
import openpyxl, os, shutil
from pathlib import Path

# Paths
input_path = "/sandbox/input/input_spreadsheet/1_39515_init.xlsx"
output_dir = Path("/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet")
output_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
output_path = output_dir / "1_39515_init.xlsx"

# Load workbook (keep formulas)
wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(input_path, data_only=False)
ws = wb[wb.sheetnames[0]]

max_row = ws.max_row
col_o = 15  # column O

# New formula template (row will be inserted via f-string)
new_formula_template = "=IF($B{r}=2022, INDEX($C{r}:$N{r}, MATCH(\"Jan\", $C$1:$N$1, 0)), INDEX($C{r}:$N{r}, MATCH($A{r}, $C$1:$N$1, 0)))"

for r in range(2, max_row + 1):
    ws.cell(row=r, column=col_o).value = new_formula_template.format(r=r)

# Save to output location
wb.save(output_path)

# Recalculate formulas using the provided tool
await recalculate(str(output_path))

# Verify by reloading with data_only and printing first few rows of column O
wb_check = openpyxl.load_workbook(output_path, data_only=True)
ws_check = wb_check[wb_check.sheetnames[0]]
print("Verification - first 5 rows of column O (values after recalculation):")
for r in range(2, min(7, ws_check.max_row + 1)):
    print(r, ws_check.cell(row=r, column=col_o).value)
```
